.SH "NAME"
pam_faildelay \- Chizzle tha delay on failure per\-application
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBpam_faildelay\&.so\fR\ 'u
\fBpam_faildelay\&.so\fR [debug] [delay=\fImicroseconds\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
pam_faildelay be a PAM module dat can be used ta set tha delay on failure per\-application\&.
.PP
If no
\fBdelay\fR
is given, pam_faildelay will use tha value of FAIL_DELAY from
/etc/login\&.defs\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
\fBdebug\fR
.RS 4
Turns on debuggin lyrics busted ta syslog\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBdelay=\fR\fB\fIN\fR\fR
.RS 4
Set tha delay on failure ta N microseconds\&.
.RE
.SH "MODULE TYPES PROVIDED"
.PP
Only the
\fBauth\fR
module type is provided\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
.PP
PAM_IGNORE
.RS 4
Delay was successful adjusted\&.
.RE
.PP
PAM_SYSTEM_ERR
.RS 4
Da specified delay was not valid\&.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Da followin example will set tha delay on failure ta 10 seconds:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
auth  optionizzle  pam_faildelay\&.so  delay=10000000
      
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
